  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. Uncertainty quantification was performed via comprehensive Monte Carlo sampling across all model inputs; distributional parameters for titanium alloy elastic modulus, cortical bone density, and interface friction coefficient were propagated through 10 000 model runs to characterize prediction intervals on stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement.",
